<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="721" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1126,929,1177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">
Body length 
<quantity box="[697,836,929,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" unit="mm" value="6.1" valueMax="7.1" valueMin="5.1">
5.1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,744,929,953]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
7.1 mm
</quantity>
. Body completely yellow or with tibiae, tarsi and/or head black. Antennomere III about 1.5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[878,891,961,985]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
3.0 times longer than anntenomere II. Pronotum transverse, 1.6 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[597,610,993,1017]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
1.8 times as wide as long, finely punctate. Elytra glabrous. Aedeagus dorsally with two thin lateral processes, incision between them very deep, reaching basal third of aedeagus, ventral side apically with or without hook-like process (
<figureCitation box="[248,330,1089,1113]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
